    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-31T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-31T20:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1040: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-31T18:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 31, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>134. Assembly met at 4 p.m., accepted resignation of Palma and Luis Chacon, then
                    elected Reina Andrade First Vice President by 50 votes to 11 for General Arisa
                    and 3 for Chief Justice Medrano. General <pb facs="0287" n="193" xml:id="pg_193"
                    /> Reyes was elected Second Vice President and General Solorzano, Third. First
                    reading was then given to President Chacon’s resignation and also to the Amresty
                    Bill. Second readings will be tomorrow and third Friday,<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d159fn11">January 2, 1931.</note> when Andrade will assume the
                    Provisional Presidency. The meeting of the Assembly was orderly and so far
                    everything has gone all right.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
